{"event": "tool_call", "tool": "replace", "args": {"file_path": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\project-overview.md", "content": "# Project Overview\n# Star Wars Lego — Greenfield\n\n**Document Version:** 1.0\n\n## 1. Project Summary\n\nThe Star Wars Lego project is a single-page application (SPA) designed as an educational web application for teaching JavaScript ES6+ and Vue.js 2.x concepts to beginner students. The project focuses on practical programming demonstrations through an interactive Star Wars Lego themed interface.\n\n## 2. Project Type\n\n**Project Type:** Greenfield Development\n**Target Domain:** Educational Technology\n**Primary Audience:** Beginner JavaScript students, web development learners, programming educators\n\n## 3. Core Objectives\n\n- Demonstrate practical application of JavaScript ES6+ concepts (functions, objects, arrays, loops)\n- Teach Vue.js 2.x reactive development patterns\n- Provide hands-on DOM manipulation experience\n- Create an engaging, interactive learning environment\n\n## 4. Technical Stack\n\n### Frontend Technologies\n- **HTML5:** Semantic markup structure\n- **CSS3:** Grid-based layouts, responsive design\n- **JavaScript ES6+:** Core programming logic\n- **Vue.js 2.x:** Reactive framework for data-binding and components\n- **Google Fonts:** Acme and Handlee typography\n- **Material Symbols:** Icon system\n\n### Architecture Pattern\n- **Pattern:** Single Page Application (SPA)\n- **Approach:** Simplified MVC with local state management\n- **State Management:** Component-level state with Vue.js reactivity\n\n## 5. Key Features\n\n### Character Gallery\n- Grid-based display of 8 classic Star Wars Lego characters\n- Interactive hover effects and modern visual transitions\n- Character information and interaction capabilities\n\n### Search System\n- Real-time filtering by character name\n- Input validation with required field enforcement\n- Dynamic content updates based on search criteria\n\n### Social Interactions\n- Like/favorite functionality for characters\n- Delete/remove characters from the display\n- Visual feedback through user-friendly alerts\n\n### Personalization\n- Customizable greeting messages\n- Dynamic title updates based on user interactions\n- Personalized user experience elements\n\n## 6. Design Specifications\n\n### Visual Theme\n- **Design Concept:** Space/Star Wars aesthetic\n- **Color Palette:**\n  - Background: Dark space theme (#111) with galaxy imagery\n  - Text: Light gray (#CCC) for readability\n  - Highlights: Star Wars yellow (#FD4) for emphasis\n  - Alerts: Red (#FF4444) for user notifications\n\n### Layout Requirements\n- **Container:** Fixed-width, centered layout\n- **Minimum Width:** 820px (desktop and tablet focus)\n- **Responsive Design:** Adaptive layouts for supported viewports\n\n## 7. Technical Constraints\n\n### Browser Compatibility\n- **Target Browsers:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (modern versions)\n- **Viewport Support:** Desktop and tablets (820px+ width)\n- **No Mobile Support:** Resolutions below 820px not supported\n\n### Performance Requirements\n- **Loading Priority:** Fast initial load with optimized resources\n- **Image Optimization:** Web-ready formats for character images\n- **Font Loading:** External Google Fonts (internet connection required)\n\n### Dependencies\n- **Runtime:** Only Google Fonts require internet connectivity\n- **Local Resources:** All other assets hosted locally\n- **No Backend:** Pure client-side application\n\n## 8. Project Assets\n\n### Image Resources\n- **Location:** C:\\QAx\\images\n- **Content:** Star Wars Lego character images\n- **Format:** Web-optimized image formats\n- **Usage:** Character gallery and interactive elements\n\n## 9. Development Timeline\n\n### Current Status\n- **Phase:** Ready for development\n- **Specification:** Complete (PRD001 v1.0)\n- **Code Structure:** Planned for modularity and maintainability\n\n### Future Enhancements\n- Additional character expansion\n- Backend/database integration\n- User authentication systems\n- Enhanced social features\n\n## 10. Quality Requirements\n\n### Educational Standards\n- Clear code documentation for learning purposes\n- Demonstrable programming concepts\n- Progressive difficulty for skill building\n- Interactive feedback mechanisms\n\n### Code Quality\n- Modular, maintainable structure\n- Component-based architecture\n- Performance optimization\n- Cross-browser compatibility\n\n---\n\n*Star Wars Lego Project Overview — Globant Delivery Team*"}}
